    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Flight Control System Overview</title>
        <para>
          The flight control system provides the crew with the means to control the
          aircraft in flight. The system consists of primary and secondary flight
          controls, which are described in the following sections.
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
      
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Primary Flight Controls</title>
        <para>
          The primary flight controls consist of:
        </para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Ailerons - Control aircraft roll (ATA 27-11)</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Elevators - Control aircraft pitch (ATA 27-31)</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Rudder - Control aircraft yaw (ATA 27-21)</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
        <para>
          These surfaces are operated through a fly-by-wire system with triple
          redundancy, ensuring safe operation even with multiple system failures.
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
      
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Secondary Flight Controls</title>
        <para>
          The secondary flight controls enhance aircraft performance and include:
        </para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Flaps - High-lift devices for takeoff and landing (ATA 27-51)</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Slats - Leading edge high-lift devices (ATA 27-81)</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Spoilers - Speed brakes and roll assist devices (ATA 27-61)</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
      
      <levelledPara>
        <title>System Architecture</title>
        <para>
          The flight control system uses a quad-redundant computing architecture
          with the following key features:
        </para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Four independent flight control computers with cross-channel monitoring</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Triple hydraulic power sources for actuator operation</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Electric backup for critical control surfaces</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Mechanical backup for elevator control</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Flight envelope protection with automatic stall prevention</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
      
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Safety Features</title>
        <para>
          The system incorporates multiple safety features in accordance with
          ARP4761 safety assessment requirements:
        </para>
        <para>
          <randomList>
            <listItem>
              <para>Redundant actuation systems (DAL A)</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Automatic fault detection and isolation</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Control surface position monitoring</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Envelope protection preventing excessive control inputs</para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>Graceful degradation with system failures</para>
            </listItem>
          </randomList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
      
